  "description": [
    "The only pipe Mr Tolbott has carved for himself would be too nerveracking as a fulltime job and too expensive to the buyer he explains Id starve between payments too since It some times takes three years to do a good pipe job Mr Talbott carves his pipe bowls until he starts thinking about something else or peo ple talk to him I can listen but talking and carving dont go well together he says Mr Talbott discovered he could wield a knife while homewardbound from Eu rope on a World War I troop ship He wanted to join a magazine trading circlethe only diversion on the boat so he offered to carve a sol diers initials on a pipe in return for a magazine Id never carved anything be fore he recalls but since then Ive never stopped All together Mr Talbott has whittled 25 pipes but only one has been for himself That one commemorates his World War I outfit the 313th Machine Gun Company of the 7th Division It bears such details as an Identification bracelet on a soldiers arm To do the detailed gouging of the soldiers facial expression meant devising special tools something he often"
